AdditionalInformation.AdditionalInformationLine: IP Roaming/Networking Information : Please note that Telstra may not advertise all IP address ranges used by PMN for connection to inter - PMN IP backbone. These ranges are reserved and are not currently advertised:
MSRNs are in the form +61 4180 xxxxx with a fixed length of 11 digits
Lycamobile MVNO makes use of Telstra numbers CC=61 NDC=469, 470
Additional NDCs : Due to Mobile Number Portability, Telstra MobileNet may also use the following number series from other Australian operators. MSISDN numbering has a fixed length of 11 digits:
Globalstar Australia : CC=61 NDC=42010, 4888 Pivotel : CC=61 NDC=4800, 4808, 4858, 4899 TPG Mobile : CC=61 NDC=42012, 4493

To enable successful delivery of SMS from your customers to Telstra MobileNet customers, please implement all of the above Additional NDCs as a GT in your mobile and international network if you do not have a roaming agreement with the above operators.
Telstra supports A5 Cipher Algorithm versions 1 and 3

Telstra NDCs 46710 – 46714 are reserved for use by Telstra M2M services and the following IMSI subrange is reserved for use by M2M services: 50501 349 (7-9), 505 01 40999, 505 01 600, 505 01 6100, 505 01 611, 505 01 62 (0-1), 505 01 6300 (0-1)
Telstra offers interworking for SMS over CAMEL for inbound roamers on Telstra networks
Telstra does not support SMS over GPRS
The roaming partner network must support CAMEL Version 2 (or above) to allow Telstra customers to roam with CAMEL on the roaming partner network.
If the roaming partner network supports only CAMEL Version 1 then CAMEL roaming for Telstra customers will not be possible on the roaming partner network.
CAMEL short codes for Telstra customers:
Telstra GSM Mobile Originated SMS +61 418 706 700 (main number translates to various GSM SMSCs). The list of SMSC GTs appears in Network Elements Information.
Telstra SGSNs support GTP Versions 0 and 1. Telstra GGSNs support GTP Version 1 only. GTP Ports in use are:
GTP UDP Source Ports = 2123, 2152, 3386 and 49152 to 65535
